data-triple-N3.o: "Rio Grande do Sul (lit. "Great Southern River") is the southernmost state in Brazil, and the state with the fourth highest Human Development Index (HDI) in the country, and the third and last in the Brazilian South Region, with by far the highest standard of living. In this state is located the southernmost city in the country, Chui, on the border with Uruguay. In the region of Bento Goncalves and Caxias do Sul, the largest wine producing center in Brazil, the attraction is Italian gastronomy."@en
